<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-17T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-17T21:00:00-05:00" n="691" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                certain <gloss type="to">American diplomatic
                                missions</gloss>.</hi><note n="11" xml:id="d691fn11">Sent to the
                                Embassies at Paris, London, Madrid, Rome, Berlin and Vienna.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-17T21:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1914, 9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s April 15th, 8 p.m. General Huerta yesterday signified his
                            willingness to have the required salute given if this Government would
                            salute the Mexican flag simultaneously.</p>
                        <p>For information of the Government to which you are accredited
                            Department’s reply is given:</p>
                        <p>[Quotation of telegram 754 of April 17, 12 m., to Chargé
                            O’Shaughnessy.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>